parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sunroof can cause alarm, distraction, and potentially lead to loss of control of the vehicle, resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Loud explosion
shattered tempered glass
glass missing from all sides of the moonroof
no apparent reason or warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Vehicle Movement in Accessory Mode
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ability to shift into gear without the engine running can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if there are children or pedestrians behind the vehicle.
symptoms: Vehicle rolls or moves in reverse gear without engine running
difficulty stopping the vehicle
locked steering wheel
no power to brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The mistaken shift into reverse gear can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if there are children or pedestrians behind the vehicle.
symptoms: Vehicle rolls or moves in reverse gear
driver knocked down or dragged
injuries or fatalities possible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to unexpected deceleration, stalling, or loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage
the vehicle decelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle stalls
the vehicle rolls and stops in the middle of the road
the transmission slips or hesitates
PCM code 6F35.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected shifting of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into park without touching the park button
loud clicking sound when shifting into park
the vehicle dies or stalls
the vehicle hesitates or slips when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the vehicle can cause unexpected loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies without warning
the vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the vehicle stalls or dies without any indication or warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Fade and Unpredictable Response
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable brake pedal response can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distance, and potential accidents, especially in low-speed situations.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels further than usual
the brake pedal sometimes goes all the way up or only halfway down
the brakes lock up
the ABS warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deactivation of the blind spot warning system can increase the risk of accidents or collisions, as the driver may not be aware of vehicles in the blind spot.
symptoms: The blind spot warning system is deactivated
the system does not alert the driver of vehicles in the blind spot
the system malfunctions when using other vehicle features (e.g.
window switches).

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress into Rear Lift Gate Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the rear lift gate assembly can cause electrical shorts, leading to malfunctioning reverse lights, which can increase the risk of accidents or citations.
symptoms: Water accumulation in the rear lift gate assembly
reverse lights remain on at all times while driving
failure to pass vehicle inspections
electrical shorts or malfunctions in the rear lift gate assembly.
